[src:apache-parquet-format/serialization] Storable includes functions to serialize and deserialize Perl data structures to and from files or Perl scalars.
[src:apache-parquet-format/serialization] In addition to serializing directly to files, `Storable` includes the `freeze` function to return a serialized copy of the data packed into a scalar, and `thaw` to deserialize such a scalar.
[src:apache-parquet-format/serialization] This is useful for sending a complex data structure over a network socket or storing it in a database.
[src:apache-parquet-format/serialization] When serializing structures with `Storable`, there are network safe functions that always store their data in a format that is readable on any computer at a small cost of speed.
[src:apache-parquet-format/serialization] These functions are named `nstore`, `nfreeze`, etc.
